
[1]soundly

   SOUND'LY, adv. [from sound, entire.]

   1. Healthily; heartily.

   2. Severely; lustily; with heavy blows; smartly; as, to beat one
   soundly.

   3. Truly; without fallacy or error; as, to judge or reason soundly.

   4. Firmly; as a doctrine soundly settled.

   5. Fast; closely; so as not to be easily awakened; as, to sleep
   soundly.
